                    </decoDesc>
                    <additions><list>
                    <item xml:id="e1"><desc>The manuscript is nicely made and heavily used, with dirt and wear patterns on the folios.</desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="e2"><desc><locus target="#ir(ecto)" facs="002"/> an exercise in letter writing. </desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="e3"><desc><locus target="#iir(ecto)"/> beginning of letter writing. </desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="e4"><desc><locus target="#iiiv(erso)"/> upper, exercise in letter writing; writing exercise from some Image. </desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="a1"><desc><locus target="#13r #13v #16r #18r #18v #27r" facs="016 017 019 021 022 031"/> notes on the occasions when the psalms should be read, some written in red ink. </desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="a2"><desc><locus target="#23r #23v" facs="026 027"/> a patch has been sown over what looks like a hole burned in the folio, with text added where it has been destroyed</desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="e5"><desc><locus target="#56r" facs="060"/> A small cross in a red circle mark the midpoint of the Psalms. </desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="a3"><desc type="ScribalSignature"><locus target="#136v" facs="141"/> Copied by Zena Marqos. </desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="e6"><desc>Status of binding is very good. </desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="e7"><desc>Condition of vellum is clean and shows virtually no cracking and only minimal discoloration.</desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="e8"><desc> Numbnered quires: quires 2–17. </desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="e9"><desc>
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#51r #59r #61r #110r" facs="055 063 065 114"/>, etc.);
                      text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#12v #31v #119v" facs="016 036 124"/>)</desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="e10"><desc>This scribe has avoided the problem of lines of text too long to fit on one line by adopting an aspect ratio that leaves
                      ample room for the width of most lines. On a few occasions, a line is still too long and has to be completed above or below the end of the line
                      (e.g., <locus target="#6v #10v #11v" facs="010 015 016"/></desc></item>
                    </list></additions>
